This paper proposes a novel procedure for training a deep neural network for neural machine translation, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of an encoder-decoder architecture, which is a common technique in deep learning and falls under the category of machine learning (ML). Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of softmax loss, which is a common technique in deep learning and falls under the category of artificial intelligence (AI). Therefore, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of a case study of neural machine translation, which involves the use of recurrent neural networks (RNNs), which falls under the category of neural networks (NE). Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is another likely sub-category. Finally, the paper also discusses the use of image captioning, which involves the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs), which falls under the category of computer vision (CV). Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is another likely sub-category.
